stories.text:
Not sure if this a bug or feature.

I searched for pro wrestling videos (I know), and mixed in with my search results where:

- cryptocurrency videos

- stock picking videos

- teenage reaction videos about random subjects

- a video about white supremacists

I really don't know what's going on. These videos have nothing to do with my search query, subscriptions or previous searches on youtube or elsewhere on Google.

They're not marked as ads either, they're just presented as straight search results - and there is no way to hide or block them.

What is going on with Youtube, are they so intent on torpedoing this business...
